Name: residual stage of open angle glaucoma
Definition: A tauopathy that is characterized by memory lapses
Synonym: Residual stage of open angle glaucoma

Name: primary open angle glaucoma
Definition: An open-angle glaucoma that is characterized by the absence of any apparent obstruction of aqueous outflow through the trabecular meshwork with gonioscopy

Name: obsolete passive-aggressive personality disorder
Definition: An open-angle glaucoma that is characterized by the absence of any apparent obstruction of aqueous outflow through the trabecular meshwork with gonioscopy

Name: obsolete meningococcal septicemia
Definition: An open-angle glaucoma that is characterized by the absence of any apparent obstruction of aqueous outflow through the trabecular meshwork with gonioscopy

Name: low tension glaucoma
Definition: A parathyroid gland disease characterized by an overactivity of the parathyroid glands
